##CONFIRMED CASE APPROACHING 10,000! The threat of a pandemic is "very real" , says World Health Organization

Micro Signal China Business Journal

Function introduction, grow in step with Chinese enterprises, talk with business leaders, spread business ideals, serve business people, "China Business News" control of the absolute voice of Chinese business.

As of 10:00 central European time on the 9th (17:00 China Standard Time on the 9th) , there were 28,673 confirmed cases of new pneumonia outside China and 686 deaths, with nearly 10,000 confirmed cases in Italy, according to the latest World Health Organization report.

To contain the spread of the disease, Italian Prime Minister Contes announced on the 9th local time night, emergency control measures will be extended to the entire Italian territory. From the 10th, the movement of people across regions is prohibited except for work or health needs. Schools across Italy remain closed until April 3, while sporting events and activities are suspended.

For the first time in Italian history, the whole country has been shut down

Local 9 night, Italian Prime Minister Contes announced, due to the new crown epidemic severity, emergency control measures will be extended to the entire Italian territory. From the 10th, if the non-work or health needs, prohibit the movement of people across the region. Schools across Italy will remain closed until April 3, while sporting events and activities will be suspended. Contes said the Italian government believed it was necessary to take drastic measures to avoid further spread of the epidemic across the country.

"All of us have to give up something for the benefit of Italy, " Contes said in his speech, "We have to make this decision now, and only if we all work together to adapt to these more stringent measures can we finally do it. "

RT in Russia called the move "unprecedented" . Rt Russia reported that Contes said there would now be no one "red zone" and that Italy as a whole would be classified as a "red zone" and no one would be allowed to leave their place of residence except for work or health reasons, a total ban on all public meetings, sporting events and activities throughout Italy. "We will no longer tolerate this kind of nightlife, " Contes said of the nationwide ban

The Italian Olympic Committee announced Thursday on its website that it will suspend domestic sports until April 3 due to the new pneumonia outbreak, which means the ongoing Serie A tournament will be suspended. International events involving clubs and national teams are outside the jurisdiction of the Italian Olympic Committee and are not affected by this decision for the time being.

According to the Global Times, an industry insider said that as a European country, Italy has taken the drastic measures to seal off cities across the country unexpectedly, making it as thorough, absolute and difficult as Wuhan. He said the Italian siege had a different meaning from that of China. The social cost of a siege is high and politically incorrect in Europe and the United States, which may be hard to emulate. Who director-general Tan Desai said March 9, different countries have different specific circumstances, the need to take targeted response measures.

People lined up at the supermarket overnight

After Italian Prime Minister Contes announced controls on the movement of people across the country, people who feared they would not be able to grab supplies turned out overnight to line up at supermarkets to stock up. According to the Italian "La Repubblica" reported that in Rome, Naples and other cities, many citizens rushed to the night-time business supermarket, the Line into the door shopping.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The Italian Prime Minister's office responded that the supply of food and daily necessities would be guaranteed, and the purchase of daily necessities would be an exception to the movement control, would not be subject to measures to obstruct or punish, and people would not have to hoard. But supermarkets across the country are still running out of pasta and canned goods.

Outbreak triggers prison riot, 20 escape, 7 dead

Riots broke out in Italian prisons in protest against the Italian government's epidemic prevention measures. The riot resulted in the escape of 20 prisoners and the death of seven.

According to a report by the Agenzia Nazionale Stampa Associata on March 9, a total of 50 prisoners escaped from Foggia prison in southern Italy during the riot on the morning of March 9. Police stopped the escape of 30 prisoners and 20 others were still at large. Meanwhile, fires broke out in two prisons in the capital, Rome, and in a prison in Province of Prato as inmates rioted. Seven prisoners have been killed in prison riots across Italy, including those who died from an overdose of psychotropic drugs and those who died from choking on fire fumes.

According to the Business Insider, as the Italian government announced on the 8th that the northern part of the country will be closed, prisoners in the prison also feel restricted, because the closure measures affect the visits of prisoners'families. In addition, because the prison is a closed space, the inmates of the new coronavirus infection panic, which led to riots.

Tandesay: The threat of a pandemic is very real

On March 9 local time, World Health Organization released the latest issue of its daily report on the condition of the new coronary pneumonia. As of 10:00 am China Standard Time, 9:00 am central European time, a total of 28,673 new cases and 202 new deaths have been confirmed in 104 countriesterritories outside China, bringing the total to 686, three more countries have reported cases to WHO, Bangladesh, Albania and Paraguay.

Who director-general Tan Desai said in a speech on the 9th that the epidemic has emerged in many countries and that the threat of a pandemic "has become very real. " He added that while the situation is grim, but the outbreak will be "the first controlled pandemic in history" 

In the four countries with the highest number of cases, Tandsey said, China's epidemic was under control. South Korea has reported fewer new cases. Both countries have shown that it is never too late to reverse the trend. He also said that Italy was taking decisive measures to control the epidemic and hoped these measures would be effective in the coming days.
